s oil ministry vs Nepal news outlet over ‘rejection’ of E20 petrol by Balen\'s govt','In ‘Fact Check’ posted on its social media accounts, ministry said: “Claims that Bhutan declined an offer to import E20 petrol from India are incorrect.” | India News','Hindustan Times','https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/indias-oil-ministry-vs-nepal-news-outlet-over-rejection-of-e20-by-balens-govt-101783251274272.html','https://www.hindustantimes.com/ht-img/img/2026/07/05/550x309/ANI-20260605321-0_1783251836048_1783251851462_35c7f790-bf4e-4080-9e0e-99eb6757d0fc.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-05 04:47:49','2026-07-12 14:26:01','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(131,40,'Centre dismisses reports of Bhutan rejecting E20 petrol proposal, says no export offer was made','Centre dismisses reports of Bhutan rejecting E20 petrol proposal, says no export offer was made - New Delhi, July 5 The Centre on Sunday rejected media reports claiming that Bhutan turned down an Indian ... Get Latest News on Technology only on lokmattimes.com','Lokmat Times','https://www.lokmattimes.com/technology/centre-dismisses-reports-of-bhutan-rejecting-e20-petrol-proposal-says-no-export-offer-was-made-1/','https://d3pc1xvrcw35tl.cloudfront.net/ln/feedImages/1200x900/202607053852642_202607.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-05 03:01:07','2026-07-12 14:26:01','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(132,40,'Centre dismisses reports of Bhutan rejecting E20 petrol proposal, says no export offer was made','Centre dismisses reports of Bhutan rejecting E20 petrol proposal, says no export offer was made - New Delhi, July 5 The Centre on Sunday rejected media reports claiming that Bhutan turned down an Indian ... Get Latest News on Business only on lokmattimes.com','Lokmat Times','https://www.lokmattimes.com/business/centre-dismisses-reports-of-bhutan-rejecting-e20-petrol-proposal-says-no-export-offer-was-made/','https://d3pc1xvrcw35tl.cloudfront.net/ln/feedImages/1200x900/202607053852642_202607.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-05 03:01:07','2026-07-12 14:26:01','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(133,40,'Govt rubbishes claim that Bhutan rejected E20 petrol import: ‘No proposal for export’','The government issued a clarification on a local report published last week, claiming that Bhutan rejected importing E20 fuel from India.','Livemint','https://www.livemint.com/news/india/govt-rubbishes-claim-that-bhutan-rejected-e20-petrol-import-no-proposal-for-export-11783243326570.html','https://www.livemint.com/lm-img/img/2026/07/05/1600x900/logo/E20_fuel_1783243818831_1783243819154_5a14ea44-c0b6-4bc0-a51c-d6d298463ad0.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-05 02:31:30','2026-07-12 14:26:01','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(134,40,'\'No such offer was made\': Centre denies report claiming Bhutan turned down E20 petrol from India','\'No such offer has been made by the Oil Marketing Companies, and there is no proposal for export of E20 petrol to Bhutan,\' says the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas','Business Today','https://www.businesstoday.in/india/story/no-such-offer-was-made-centre-denies-report-claiming-bhutan-turned-down-e20-petrol-from-india-541032-2026-07-05','https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/businesstoday/images/story/202607/6a49f9c85233c-govt-rejects-reports-on-bhutan-refusing-e20-petrol-from-india-052922514-16x9.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-04 23:30:58','2026-07-12 14:26:01','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(135,35,'Fidelity of the implementation of antirabies vaccination for dogs and cats in the Plurinational State of Bolivia','Author summary Rabies is a fatal but preventable disease that disproportionately affects vulnerable populations in low-resource settings. Vaccinating dogs and cats is the most effective strategy for preventing human rabies, yet transmission persists in some endemic countries, including Bolivia. In this study, we evaluated how well a mass rabies vaccination campaign was implemented in a high-risk area of Cochabamba. We found that none of the 17 health centers fully adhered to national guidelines, revealing critical gaps in implementation. Major challenges included inadequate cold chain infrastructure, insufficient personnel, weak interinstitutional coordination, and limited communication with communities. Despite these barriers, both health workers and pet owners recognized rabies as a serious threat and expressed a willingness to support control efforts. Our findings highlight that the main barrier to eliminating rabies is not the lack of effective tools but the difficulty of delivering them consistently under real-world conditions. Strengthening coordination across the human and animal health sectors, improving logistics, and enhancing community engagement are essential for increasing vaccination coverage. Addressing these implementation gaps is critical to advancing rabies elimination and protecting both human and animal health.','PLOS (Public Library of Science)','https://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pntd.0014535','https://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article/figure/image?id=10.1371/journal.pntd.0014535.g004&size=inline','Logistics','Positive',2,0,'2026-07-09 17:00:00','2026-07-12 14:26:04','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(136,35,'Bolivia’s Paz Pushes Industry Reforms After 53 Days of Protests','As Bolivians try to resume a sense of normalcy after 53 days of blockades that roiled the economy, President Rodrigo Paz is right back where he was just two months ago: attempting to reform the nationalistic laws that dictate the country’s key industries.','Bloomberg','https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-06-27/bolivia-s-rodrigo-paz-pushes-mining-hydrocarbons-reform-after-blockades','https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/infgveq6jnpw/v0/1200x800.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-27 07:30:00','2026-07-12 14:26:04','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(137,35,'Bolivia\'s Bold Currency Shift: From Dollar Peg to Flexibility','Bolivia ends its 15-year dollar peg, devaluing its currency in a policy shift aimed at economic stability. The move facilitates a potential $3 billion IMF program but faces opposition from labor groups concerned about austerity measures. The government insists on external financing to stabilize its economy.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3941616-bolivias-bold-currency-shift-from-dollar-peg-to-flexibility','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/01_07_2024_22_10_36_0842232.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-26 17:43:36','2026-07-12 14:26:04','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(138,35,'World News Today Live Updates on June 21, 2026 : Why Bolivia declared state of emergency amid protests? US Defence Chief Pete Hegseth warns ‘United States is watching’','World News Today highlights on June 21, 2026: Stay informed on global events with our in-depth world news coverage, bringing you the latest developments across politics, economy, and culture. Discover insights into international affairs, breaking news, and the trends shaping our interconnected world, all in one place.','Livemint','https://www.livemint.com/news/world/total-world-latest-news-on-june-21-2026-live-updates-11782007264044.html','https://www.livemint.com/lm-img/img/2026/06/21/1600x900/logo/BOLIVIA-PROTEST-EMERGENCY-4_1782047752033_1782047803325_c9c785c2-7352-4d55-8805-3f2c877e84e2.JPG','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-20 19:01:03','2026-07-12 14:26:04','2026-07-16 10:09:16'),(139,35,'Bolivia on edge after Paz declares emergency to clear protest gridlock','Bolivian President Rodrigo Paz declared a state of emergency, allowing security forces to clear protesters\' roadblocks, after 50 days of protests that have left 14 dead and crippled the economy.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/politics/3938101-bolivia-on-edge-after-paz-declares-emergency-to-clear-protest-gridlock','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/20_10_2025_16_00_00