sanctions levied by the Trump administration against the communist-run government. As services break down','ABC17News.com','https://abc17news.com/news/national-world/cnn-world/2026/07/06/cubas-hotels-sit-empty-as-us-pressure-campaign-drives-tourists-away/','https://abc17news.b-cdn.net/abc17news.com/2026/07/cnn-L19jb21wb25lbnRzL2ltYWdlL2luc3RhbmNlcy9jbXF2N3lmY3AwMDAwM2I2cnZxMXVrd3Vy-L19jb21wb25lbnRzL2FydGljbGUvaW5zdGFuY2VzL2NtcXY2aWQxZjAwNm0yZHA2ZXJzdmZ1MzM-scaled.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-06 03:00:26','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(251,57,'\'Send them to Iran\': Karoline Leavitt\'s viral Gen Z rant ignites fierce social media debate','Karoline Leavitt suggested sending young Americans complaining about the economy to Iran or Cuba during a Fox News appearance.','Hindustan Times','https://www.hindustantimes.com/trending/us/send-them-to-iran-karoline-leavitts-viral-gen-z-rant-ignites-fierce-social-media-debate-101783108867329.html','https://www.hindustantimes.com/ht-img/img/2026/07/03/550x309/Trump-Triumphal-Arch-0_1783108846595_1783108863668_c84cedc7-8c9b-4f71-8710-fb0d11196ddf.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-03 16:08:58','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(252,57,'Cuba-U.S. Dialogue Hits Stalemate Amidst Ongoing Sanctions','Cuba\'s foreign minister announced that talks with the U.S. have stalled, dimming hopes of easing sanctions impacting Cuba\'s economy. Accusations include U.S. attempts to pressure the UN over an upcoming debate on the blockade. Despite reforms, Cuba insists these changes are independent of external influences.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/politics/3943176-cuba-us-dialogue-hits-stalemate-amidst-ongoing-sanctions','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/03_07_2025_15_48_54_341133.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 09:21:12','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(253,57,'Cuba says US pressuring UN member states to put off trade embargo debate','HAVANA, June 30 - Cuba\'s foreign minister said on Tuesday that the U.S. State Department was \\\"pressuring and intimidating\\\" United Nations member states to put off an upcoming floor debate over the U.S. blockade of the communist-run island. Read more at straitstimes.com.','The Straits Times','https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/cuba-says-us-pressuring-un-member-states-to-put-off-trade-embargo-debate','https://cassette.sphdigital.com.sg/image/straitstimes/3d831d14462223bd1582367cfeec833153d9ae7eb4f3fb3b57d52d051c961b74','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 08:40:28','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(254,57,'Cuba\'s top diplomat says talks with United States showing \'no progress\'','Cuba\'s foreign minister said on Tuesday that talks initiated earlier this year with long-time foe the United States had stalled, leaving little hope for an end to U.S. sanctions that have laid siege to the island\'s ailing economy.','Reuters','https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/cuba-accuses-us-pressuring-un-member-states-put-off-trade-embargo-debate-2026-06-30/','https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/QS67EVX3VBKS5PX2RAQK5QTA4M.jpg?auth=8a1e8edc07db08c18b79583bc1a28d6faa51a24de2dd0ff5fb3d9bc666014fb8&height=1005&width=1920&quality=80&smart=true','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 08:36:54','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(255,57,'US slaps new sanctions on Cuban companies key to island\'s crumbling economy','The U.S. government has slapped additional sanctions on Cuban companies that are expected to spook foreign investors and deepen a severe economic crisis. U.S. Secretary of State Marco Rubio said Tuesday that the sanctions target five Cuban entities. Three are linked to GAESA, a business conglomerate operated by Cuba’s Revolutionary Armed Forces. Rubio accused what he called “regime elites” of using GAESA to “steal the island’s few resources, diverting them for repression, anti-American subversion and spying.\" The Cuban government did not immediately respond to a request for comment. Anyone that provides services to the targeted Cuban entities risks being cut off from the U.S. financial system.','The Atlanta Journal-Constitution','https://www.ajc.com/news/2026/06/us-slaps-new-sanctions-on-cuban-companies-key-to-islands-crumbling-economy/','https://images.ajc.com/resizer/v2/OLR7JVMIUZDWDLKEIRIUR3EMWE.jpg?auth=e24abf988dc2023b009bfd53cca175e31a21783aa58b0897dd36b2a7a5f3024e&width=1200&height=630&smart=true','Economy','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-23 14:12:17','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(256,57,'U.S. slaps new sanctions on Cuban companies key to island\'s crumbling economy','Secretary of State Marco Rubio said the sanctions target five Cuban entities, including three linked to Grupo de Administración Empresarial S.A., a business conglomerate operated by Cuba’s Revolutionary Armed Forces.','Los Angeles Times','https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2026-06-23/u-s-slaps-new-sanctions-on-cuban-companies-key-to-islands-crumbling-economy','https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/78d9cf8/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4001x2101+0+283/resize/1200x630!/quality/75/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2Fa2%2F8ed818c448109725694399cbb9db%2F79ab658237c14220a7ad','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-23 10:48:28','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(257,57,'The next Cuba crisis? Puerto Rico’s corruption is a grave risk to America','Puerto Rico, a failing U.S. jurisdiction in the shadow of Venezuela, Cuba, and China, threatens to export migration surges, narcotics, and radicalization.','Washington Examiner','https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/op-eds/4618265/cuba-crisis-puerto-rico-corruption-risk/','https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/image-collage-c5269czo4-1782096491656-e1782136456932.jpg?1782082195&resize=1200,683','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-23 03:00:00','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(258,57,'Cuba makes sweeping market-liberalisation reforms in face of Trump pressure','Communist Party signs off on list of 176 measures as the Cuban govt tries to rescue a moribund economy that’s being squeezed by US sanctions.','ThePrint','https://theprint.in/world/cuba-makes-sweeping-market-liberalisation-reforms-in-face-of-trump-pressure/2965494/','https://staticprintenglish.theprint.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/458738736-scaled-e1781955807234.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-20 04:45:13','2026-07-12 14:31:05','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(259,58,'Haiti at FIFA World Cup 2026: A war escape, a ghost coach and 52 years of waiting','On the night Haiti qualified, their players were not in Haiti. They were in Curacao — a Dutch island off the coast of Venezuela, 500 miles from home — because armed gangs control most of Port-au-Prince and the national stadium sits unusable.','The Indian Express','https://indianexpress.com/shorts/sports/football/haiti-fifa-world-cup-2026-war-coach-wait-10737506/','https://images.indianexpress.com/2026/06/haiti-ap.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-12 23:37:00','2026-07-12 14:31:07','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(260,61,'Cypriot natural gas could start flowing from ExxonMobil\'s discoveries by 2033','Natural gas could start flowing from two undersea deposits ExxonMobil discovered off Cyprus by 2033, the company\'s Vice President of Global Exploration John Ardill said, helping to turn the east Mediterranean island nation into a new European energy hub. Ardill said Tuesday that the largest U.S. oil company and consortium partner QatarEnergy consider the most likely option for getting the gas to market to be conveying it through a pipeline to existing processing facilities in Egypt where it can be liquefied for export. Other options, such as building onshore facilities in Cyprus or a floating one over the deposits, are considered too costly.','The Atlanta Journal-Constitution','https://www.ajc.com/news/2026/06/cypriot-natural-gas-could-start-flowing-from-exxonmobils-discoveries-by-2033/','https://images.ajc.com/resizer/v2/E2BWEUPQHJCU7ODGOV5KSBPZZ4.jpg?auth=72e3a6b386d1c0a13af883da7b647a9ef26b85681c4cdf68563ecf3e54aec628&width=1200&height=630&smart=true','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 06:12:11','2026-07-12 14:31:10','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(261,61,'Castor Maritime Inc. Announces Vessel Acquisition','LIMASSOL, Cyprus, June 22, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Castor Maritime Inc. (NASDAQ: CTRM), (\'Castor” or the \'Company”), a diversified global shipping and energy company, announces that it has entered into an agreement, through a separate wholly-owned subsidiary, to acquire a 2023-built modern-eco Kamsarmax bulk carrier vessel from an unaffiliated third party for a purchase price of $37.5 million.','The Manila Times','https://www.manilatimes.net/2026/06/22/tmt-newswire/globenewswire/castor-maritime-inc-announces-vessel-acquisition/2370017','https://manilatimes.net/manilatimes/uploads/images/2026/06/22/1108212.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-22 04:49:03','2026-07-12 14:31:10','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(262,61,'Europe explores energy security alternatives after Iran war’s turmoil','NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) — The Iran war \'s shock to global fuel prices has reinforced Europe\'s stance that it must forge alternative trade and energy routes to the…','WTOP','https://wtop.com/europe/2026/06/europe-explores-energy-security-alternatives-after-iran-wars-turmoil/','https://wtop.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/wtop_logo_512x512.png','Trade','Negative',0,2,'2026-06-17 19:27:28','2026-07-12 14:31:10','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(263,61,'Leveraged Launches the Leveraged Cup to Trade Your Way to the World Football Final in New York','Limassol, Cyprus, June 16th, 2026, ChainwireLeveraged, a prop trading firm empowering anyone to become a trader, announced the launch of the 2026 Leveraged Cup, a trading competition running from June 17-30. The overall','Benzinga','https://www.benzinga.com/pressreleases/