630,imgsize-83522,overlay-economictimes/articleshow.jpg','Trade','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-09 08:18:00','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(342,1,'Germany could gain from planned U.S. port fees on China-built ships, DIW says','Germany could benefit from planned U.S. port fees on merchant ships ​built in China, with its exports to the ‌United States potentially rising by around 2% compared with a scenario without fees, according to a study by the German Institute ​for Economic Research (DIW) seen by Reuters on Wednesday.','Reuters','https://www.reuters.com/world/china/germany-could-gain-planned-us-port-fees-china-built-ships-diw-says-2026-07-08/','https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/K4YZ5QJLBZKGLHDAONVMQZHSH4.jpg?auth=95c2c9f6722778b295d873eb5f1d6cc749a1ab7723c012cc8362a5c14929542e&height=1005&width=1920&quality=80&smart=true','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-07 22:32:16','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(343,1,'U.S. Port Fees Propel Germany\'s Export Advantage','A study suggests Germany could see a 2% boost in exports to the U.S. due to planned port fees on Chinese-built ships. The fees aim to counter China\'s shipbuilding dominance but may inadvertently harm U.S. competitiveness while benefiting nations like Germany, which rely less on Chinese vessels.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3946979-us-port-fees-propel-germanys-export-advantage','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/07_07_2025_07_40_13_3481523.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-07 22:30:35','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(344,1,'Germany Clinches Landmark Submarine Deal with Canada','Germany\'s TKMS has been selected by Canada to build up to 12 submarines, a deal that boosts Germany\'s economy and strengthens NATO ties. The contract, which may generate C$167 billion in economic activity, highlights the strategic partnership between Canada, Germany, and Norway, enhancing transatlantic cooperation.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3946637-germany-clinches-landmark-submarine-deal-with-canada','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/16_07_2025_18_28_07_0887094.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-07 08:00:38','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(345,1,'Germany Plans $1.7 Billion Strategic Natural Gas Reserve','Germany\'s Economy Ministry plans a state-owned emergency gas reserve worth up to $1.7 billion as storage refills lag behind schedule.','OilPrice','https://oilprice.com/Latest-Energy-News/World-News/Germany-Plans-17-Billion-Strategic-Natural-Gas-Reserve.html','https://d32r1sh890xpii.cloudfront.net/news/1200x675/2026-07-07_qr65xzlfch.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-07 06:30:00','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(346,1,'Germany Wins Big as Canada Chooses TKMS for Submarine Deal','Germany\'s TKMS has been selected by Canada to construct up to 12 submarines, marking a significant boost for Germany\'s economy and reinforcing NATO alliances. The decision, announced at a NATO summit in Ankara, is seen as a strategic move tying Canada, Germany, and Norway together for future collaborations.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3946565-germany-wins-big-as-canada-chooses-tkms-for-submarine-deal','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/imagegallery/29_02_2020_19_18_39_4765366.jpg&width=920&format=jpeg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-07 06:21:49','2026-07-12 14:35:47','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(347,1,'Germany Plans Strategic Gas Reserve to Bolster Energy Security','Germany\'s Economy Ministry is creating a state-owned strategic gas reserve, costing up to €1.5 billion, for emergencies like infrastructure sabotage. Set to hold 24 TWh of gas, it\'s part of an energy security effort post-Russia\'s Ukraine invasion. Approv