ources said.','Reuters','https://www.reuters.com/business/energy/russia-asks-kazakhstan-gasoline-ease-shortages-sources-say-2026-06-24/','https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/XGGJSNT5GVPFBP6TVDBXJKVQYQ.jpg?auth=c729060b5dc7badb5ac5543e643368f0759c5ebb34976668a2ea61b422c9e8ad&height=1005&width=1920&quality=80&smart=true','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-24 06:17:04','2026-07-14 04:09:28','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(531,121,'MAIRE steps up SAF push, deal with Kazakhstan\'s sovereign wealth fund','MAIRE Spa said Wednesday it has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Kazakhstan\'s sovereign wealth fund, Samruk-Kazyna, and the Italo-Kazakh Trade Association, to work together on developing a...','MarketScreener','https://www.marketscreener.com/news/maire-steps-up-saf-push-deal-with-kazakhstan-s-sovereign-wealth-fund-ce7f5fdbda8cf725','https://www.marketscreener.com/images/twitter_MS_fdblanc.png','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-23 22:53:27','2026-07-14 04:09:28','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(532,122,'Kenya economy to grow 4.3% in 2026, 4.4% in 2027 - World Bank','Kenya\'s economy is expected to expand 4.3% this year and 4.4% in 2027, the World Bank said on Thursday, with this year\'s forecast ​being 0.6 percentage points lower than its November prediction due to ‌the impact of the U.S.-Israeli war on Iran.','Reuters','https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/kenya-economy-grow-43-2026-44-2027-world-bank-2026-07-09/','https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/JXAWPU4SE5OVVJ7MX7AST5TCBU.jpg?auth=69f8628c0d9395327c35d61d36b80d4c651f88d19f33aff72455a309c121e0de&height=1005&width=1920&quality=80&smart=true','Economy','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-09 05:01:02','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(533,122,'Kenya economy to grow 4.3% in 2026, 4.4% in 2027 - World Bank','Kenya\'s economy is forecast to expand 4.3% this year and 4.4% in 2027, with the World Bank citing the U.S.-Israeli war on Iran as a key downward revision factor.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3947832-kenya-economy-to-grow-43-in-2026-44-in-2027---world-bank','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/31_07_2024_05_33_08_9475048.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Economy','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-09 04:57:40','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(534,122,'WTO and OIF Report Highlights Digital Trade\'s Growth Potential','Titled Digital Trade and Regulatory Frameworks: Drivers of Inclusive Growth, the report draws on research from five WTO Chairs Programme institutions representing Benin, Cameroon, Kenya, Morocco, and Mauritius.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3944591-wto-and-oif-report-highlights-digital-trades-growth-potential','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/imagegallery/22_07_2020_12_15_57_9270441.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Positive',2,0,'2026-07-02 23:46:14','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(535,122,'How Kenya and Rwanda\'s Fuel Import Framework Could Reshape East Africa\'s Energy Landscape','Kenya and Rwanda\'s new government-backed fuel import framework aims to strengthen regional energy security, improve supply chain efficiency, and deepen East African economic integration through coordinated petroleum logistics. If implemented effectively, the partnership could enhance Kenya\'s role as a regional energy hub while improving Rwanda\'s fuel supply resilience and creating new opportunities for businesses and policymakers.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/other/3942769-how-kenya-and-rwandas-fuel-import-framework-could-reshape-east-africas-energy-landscape','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/30_06_2026_11_50_05_6573822.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Positive',2,0,'2026-07-01 03:11:53','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(536,122,'Kenya, Rwanda sign fuel import deal to boost supply security','Kenya and Rwanda signed three pacts on Monday setting up a government framework for Rwanda-bound fuel imports, the Kenya Pipeline Company and Rwanda\'s Trade Ministry said in statements on X.\n...\n-June 30, 2026 at 01:30 am EDT\n- MarketScreener','MarketScreener','https://www.marketscreener.com/news/kenya-rwanda-sign-fuel-import-deal-to-boost-supply-security-ce7f5fdfd08af32c','https://cdn.zonebourse.com/static/resize/0/0//images/reuters/2026-06/2026-06-30T053252Z_1_LYNXMPEM5T0AY_RTROPTP_4_IRAN-CRISIS-KENYA-FUEL.JPG','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 22:30:26','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(537,122,'Kenya and Rwanda Forge Path for Fuel Import Framework','The governments of Kenya and Rwanda have signed three significant agreements to establish a framework for the import of fuel into Rwanda. This collaborative effort involves the Kenya Pipeline Company and Rwanda\'s Trade Ministry, as confirmed in official statements released on platform X.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3942748-kenya-and-rwanda-forge-path-for-fuel-import-framework','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/22_06_2024_13_30_27_2266721.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 22:30:01','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(538,122,'Iran war strains economy reliant on foreign help','Steve Geoffrey, one of roughly 30 million foreign nationals in the Middle East, considers himself lucky to still be able to support his family in Kenya.','Arkansas Online','https://www.arkansasonline.com/news/2026/jun/28/iran-war-strains-economy-reliant-on-foreign-help/','https://wehco.media.clients.ellingtoncms.com/imports/adg/photos/213131920_gulf-remittances-bg_42NKHMHSSFH5ZDAUOIA6NCQYDU_t1200.jpg?57a0c2296240c280e9492005c3cad63e7cbe80f4','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-28 00:45:00','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(539,122,'Remittance Of $124 Billion Stuck At Largest Migration Corridors Due To Iran War','While remittances surged early in the conflict, recent reports indicate a slowdown, particularly affecting countries like the Philippines and Kenya, which rely heavily on these funds for economic stability., Economy, Times Now','Times Now','https://www.timesnownews.com/business-economy/economy/remittance-of-124-billion-stuck-at-largest-migration-corridors-due-to-iran-war-article-154724726','https://images.timesnownews.com/thumb/msid-154724726,width-1280,height-720,resizemode-75/154724726.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-22 05:10:07','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(540,122,'Kenya taps TDB, AFC to arrange $1.2 billion airport expansion finance','Kenya has contracted Africa\'s Trade and Development Bank and Africa Finance Corporation to arrange financing for a $1.2 billion ​expansion of its main airport in Nairobi, the transport ‌minister said.','Reuters','https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/kenya-taps-tdb-afc-arrange-12-billion-airport-expansion-finance-2026-06-19/','https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/466BJJQ7PVGY5O53NZ3KL65MHM.png?auth=b9c3bf166c40a6778eb5672993fde7c30a15f48329026674eff92afd8da1d0ca&height=1005&width=1920&quality=80&smart=true','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-19 02:21:20','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(541,122,'Kenya taps TDB, AFC to arrange $1.2 billion airport expansion finance','Kenya has contracted Africa\'s Trade and Development Bank and Africa Finance Corporation to arrange financing for a $1.2 billion expansion of its main airport in Nairobi, the transport minister...\n-June 19, 2026 at 05:19 am EDT\n- MarketScreener','MarketScreener','https://www.marketscreener.com/news/kenya-taps-tdb-afc-to-arrange-1-2-billion-airport-expansion-finance-ce7f5cd2dd89f42c','https://www.marketscreener.com/images/twitter_MS_fdblanc.png','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-19 02:19:39','2026-07-14 04:09:31','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(542,129,'Trump says US reinstates blockade of Iranian shipping, but Strait of Hormuz to remain open','Trump declared a US blockade of Iranian shipping and plans to charge a 20% fee for passage through the Strait of Hormuz following recent missile and.Donald Trump, Strait of Hormuz, Iran shipping blockade, US Iran conflict, Gulf shipping crisis, Hormuz Strait fee, Iranian blockade, Truth Social, oil prices, Brent crude, US Central Command, Iran missile attacks, Iran drone attacks, Gulf tensions, Hormuz shipping route, global oil supply, Iran Revolutionary Guards, Bahrain missile interception, Kuwait US bases, Oman radar systems, Prince Hassan Air Base, Qeshm, Bandar Abbas, Abadan attack, US Iran ceasefire, Mohammad Baqer Qalibaf, Esmaeil Baghaei, MarineTraffic, freedom of navigation, international shipping, UN shipping agency, Iran Oman mechanism, Middle East conflict, energy security, oil market disruption, Gulf crisis, US foreign policy, Iran war news','Malayala Manorama','https://www.onmanorama.com/news/world/2026/07/13/trump-says-us-reinstates-blockade-of-iranian-shipping-in-hormuz.html','https://img.onmanorama.com/content/dam/mm/en/archive/news/world/images/2026/6/10/donald-trump.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,3,'2026-07-13 11:06:44','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(543,129,'Trump reimposes US blockade and demands 20% Hormuz shipping fee','Trump declared the US would collect a 20% fee on all Hormuz cargo as \"Guardian of the Strait,\" flipping the script on Iran\'s own toll demands, while US forces struck dozens of targets in Iran and the IRGC hit Bahrain, Jordan, Kuwait and Oman in the biggest exchange since the April ceasefire.','Euronews','https://www.euronews.com/2026/07/13/trump-reimposes-us-blockade-and-demands-20-hormuz-shipping-fee','https://images.euronews.com/articles/stories/09/83/65/32/1200x675_cmsv2_16632f1c-7d1d-52b4-85a9-452cb5bb5847-9836532.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-13 09:34:00','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(544,129,'US and Iran trade strikes as ceasefire comes under growing strain','Iran’s IRGC says it attacked sites linked to the US military in Kuwait, Bahrain and Oman after latest US bombardment.','Al Jazeera','https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/13/us-and-iran-trade-strikes-as-ceasefire-comes-under-growing-strain','https://www.aljazeera.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/2026-07-13T034404Z_15392971_RC2RCMAAB9QI_RTRMADP_3_IRAN-CRISIS-1783929758.jpg?resize=1920%2C1440','Trade','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-13 02:01:48','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(545,129,'Iran’s drones, coastal radar hit in ‘new wave’ of US attacks','The US military launched a new wave of strikes on Iran, targeting multiple locations with precision munitions to degrade their ability to attack international shipping in the Strait of Hormuz. Iran’s Revolutionary Guards retaliated by hitting US military targets in Jordan, Bahrain, and Kuwait.','The Indian Express','https://indianexpress.com/shorts/world/us-fresh-strikes-iran-targets-10783851-2/','https://images.indianexpress.com/2026/07/Photo-2026-07-13T091556.654.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-12 22:50:36','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(546,129,'US and Iran trade fire as tensions rise over Strait of Hormuz','Within hours of the latest US attacks, Iran said it had struck US military assets in Kuwait, Jordan, Bahrain and Oman.','BBC News','https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cevlr112pmgo','https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/d4de/live/c5c18020-7eb1-11f1-b976-0b9c15b0ccfc.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-12 21:06:21','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(547,129,'Fresh US strikes hit Iran amid renewed fighting over Strait of Hormuz','US forces retaliated with strikes after Iran attacked shipping in the Strait of Hormuz, escalating conflict that threatens peace talks and impacts.Strait of Hormuz, US military strikes Iran, Iran conflict, Middle East tensions, oil prices, global economy, Kuwait attack, Iranian Revolutionary Guards, maritime security, diplomatic solution, international relations, Middle East politics, conflict escalation, navigation freedom, conflict aftermath','Malayala Manorama','https://www.onmanorama.com/news/world/2026/07/13/us-launches-strikes-iran-hormuz.html','https://img.onmanorama.com/content/dam/mm/en/archive/news/world/images/2026/3/2/strait-of-hormuz.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,3,'2026-07-12 18:50:51','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(548,129,'US strikes Iran again as it tries to limit attacks on ships in Strait of Hormuz','The US attacked Iran early on Sunday over an Iranian strike on a container ship in the Strait of Hormuz that set it ablaze and left one crew member missing.Iran responded with attacks on several countries in the Middle East, including Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Jordan and Oman — the country on the other side of the strait, which Tehran wants to join it in managing traffic there.The US struck again later on Sunday. Iran’s state-run IRNA news agency cited the governor of Qeshm island near the strait as saying projectiles had been fired at military targets, with no casualties. IRNA said explosions were also heard in the coastal city of Bandar Abbas and Hajiabad city to the north.The Strait of Hormuz is open to all vessels seeking to lawfully transit the international waterway. U.S. forces are positioned and prepared to ensure that freedom of navigation remains available despite unwarranted Iranian aggression, harassment, threats, and arbitrary… pic.twitter.com/FS3TUBOZEj— U.S. Central Command (@CENTCOM) July 12, 2026A US official said a few strikes were conducted on missile and air defence systems, as well as small boats of the paramilitary Revolutionary Guard at a couple of locations around the strait to further degrade Iran’s ability to attack commercial shipping.Iran and the US are nearly at the midway point of the 60-day period of their interim deal aimed at reaching a permanent end to the war. The strait, a key route for the global supply of oil and natural gas and long considered an international waterway, has become a sticking point in negotiations that seem in danger of collapse.“A return to full-scale hostilities would have catastrophic consequences,” United Nations secretary-general Antonio Guterres said, according to a statement.The US military’s central command said it hit some 140 targets, including missile and drone launch sites, ammunition dumps, communication equipment and other sites.It said the attacks, heavier than in recent days, would weaken Iran’s ability to threaten shipping.“We bombed the hell out of them last night,” US President Donald Trump told NBC’s Meet The Press.Semi-official Iranian news agencies reported that a navy officer was killed.Iran retaliated by attacking nations in the region hosting US military forces, while insisting it alone must control the strait and potentially charge vessels for travelling through it.“The era of one-sided deals is OVER,” Mohammad Bagher Qalibaf, the speaker of Iran’s parliament and a main negotiator, wrote.“We told you: keep your word or pay the price. Reality is knocking.”🚫 CLAIM: The Iranian commander for the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps-Navy recently said on state-owned media that no foreign vessels may pass through the Strait of Hormuz without being identified, tracked, and monitored by Iranian forces.✅ FACT: Iran does not control the… pic.twitter.com/8lRDNiOpXQ— U.S. Central Command (@CENTCOM) July 12, 2026The US has launched three rounds of airstrikes targeting Iran in the last week over Iranian attacks on ships heading through the strait using a route off Oman, seeking to avoid the Islamic Republic’s territorial waters.The US military and Mr Trump asserted that the strait remained open on Sunday.Iran said the strait was closed until calm is restored, and it would consider targeting “additional enemy bases in the region” if it faced more attacks.The US military said more than 140 ships had transited the strait over the past week.A multinational body overseen by the US navy said traffic continued “at reduced levels” off both Oman and Iran.It said nearly 140 vessels transited daily before the war.About a fifth of all traded oil and natural gas passed through the strait before the war began.UKMTO WARNING 083-26 UPDATE 002Click here to view the full warning.⤵️https://t.co/NQPonZ9qDG#MaritimeSecurity #MarSec pic.twitter.com/00MKowQ28C— UKMTO Operations Centre (@UK_MTO) July 12, 2026Iran’s grip on it led to a global energy crisis, although oil prices have sharply dropped since wartime highs of 120 US dollars a barrel.Missile alerts sounded across several Gulf Arab countries early on Sunday.Qatar’s military said it intercepted incoming Iranian fire, with explosions heard in the neighbouring United Arab Emirates.Three people, including a child, were wounded as a result of shrapnel from the interception of Iranian attacks, Qatar’s interior ministry said, giving no further details on their condition.Missile alerts sounded in Bahrain, an island kingdom in the Persian Gulf home to the US navy’s 5th Fleet.Kuwait’s military also said it was intercepting incoming fire.The Omani state news agency said drones struck sites in an area that sits on the Strait of Hormuz and issued a shelter-in-place warning for residents in the region.The attack came a day after Oman and Iran held talks on the strait.Oman summoned the Iranian ambassador to protest against the strikes, the first such move since the war began, calling Iran’s acts “irresponsible”.Three Iranian missiles struck areas across Jordan, causing minor damage but no injuries, Jordan’s state news agency reported.Sirens also sounded in the UAE, but the government said missiles did not cross into its territory.A Cyprus-flagged container ship was hit by Iran and suffered “significant engine-room damage”, the US central command said.Oman’s maritime authority said it rescued 23 crew members but one was missing.India’s ministry of external affairs said the missing man is an Indian national and it was working with Oman to locate him.The United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations centre, overseen by the military, said the ship had been hugging Oman’s shoreline.Iran’s paramilitary Revolutionary Guard said multiple vessels “disregarded our warnings” and ignored instructions to follow what it called an approved route. One “was struck by a warning shot and brought to a stop”.JMIC Advisory Note: 014-26 Click here to view the full advisory note⤵️ https://t.co/8GmvndmpTA#MaritimeSecurity #MarSec pic.twitter.com/TXe0hiIKun— UKMTO Operations Centre (@UK_MTO) July 12, 2026Iranian state media later reported US strikes across the country, including southern Iran in the province closest to the strait and military sites in a province near Tehran.The strait sits in both Iran and Oman’s territorial waters.Oman said on Saturday that it and Iran had agreed to continue discussing the strait “at the technical and political levels”.Iran offered no statement about the strait being open to all, something sought by the Trump administration.Mr Trump suggested last week that the interim deal in the war was “over”.But mediators, including Pakistan, Qatar and Egypt, have continued efforts to reach an agreement.A regional official involved in the mediation said efforts to shore up the ceasefire continued on Sunday.Pakistan said its foreign minister had spoken by phone with Iran’s top diplomat and urged “de-escalation” on both sides.Iran’s new supreme leader, Ayatollah Mojtaba Khamenei, unseen since the war began, vowed on Saturday in his first statement since the funeral of his father, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, that Iranians would avenge his killing in the war’s opening strikes on February 28.','BreakingNews.ie','https://www.breakingnews.ie/world/us-strikes-iran-again-as-it-tries-to-limit-attacks-on-ships-in-strait-of-hormuz-1925656.html','https://img.resized.co/breaking-news/eyJkYXRhIjoie1widXJsXCI6XCJodHRwczpcXFwvXFxcL2ltYWdlcy5icmVha2luZ25ld3MuaWVcXFwvcHJvZFxcXC91cGxvYWRzXFxcLzIwMjZcXFwvMDdcXFwvMTIxMzUzMTdcXFwvYTcyM2Q2Y2Y0NGU5NDkyM2EwOWNkYTI1ZDkwZWVkZDUtMTMuanBnXCIsXCJ3aWR0aFwiOjEyMDAsXC','Logistics','Negative',0,14,'2026-07-12 13:17:39','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(549,129,'US-Iran War Live: UAE calls Iran tanker strike that killed Indian crew member a brazen violation','US-Iran War Live Updates: Fighting between the United States and Iran has intensified sharply, with both sides exchanging fresh missile and drone strikes on Monday. Iran says it has once again closed the strategically vital Strait of Hormuz, while the US insists the international waterway remains open to commercial shipping. The latest attacks have reached Qatar, Kuwait, Oman, Jordan, the United Arab Emirates and Bahrain, raising fears of a wider regional conflict. Washington has carried out fresh strikes on Iranian military targets around Hormuz, while Tehran has targeted US-linked military facilities across the Gulf and vowed to defend the key shipping route. The renewed violence has cast serious doubt on last month\'s interim US-Iran agreement, which was intended to reopen the strait and pave the way for a broader peace deal after 60 days of negotiations. President Donald Trump has declared the ceasefire effectively over, even as he says he remains open to talks. The escalating conflict has also disrupted one of the world\'s busiest energy corridors, pushing up oil prices and raising concerns over global trade. Iran has warned ships not to enter the strait without its approval, while the US says its forces are positioned to protect freedom of navigation. As military operations continue, Gulf nations are dealing with missile and drone attacks, civilian injuries and damage to critical infrastructure, while diplomatic efforts led by Oman, Qatar and other regional partners struggle to keep pace. Follow IndiaToday.in for the latest developments, key statements and real-time analysis from the rapidly evolving US-Iran conflict.','India Today','https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/us-iran-war-live-updates-strait-of-hormuz-middle-east-tensions-ceasefire-donald-trump-west-asia-crisis-2946436-2026-07-13','https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/breaking_news/202607/us-iran-war-131233607-16x9_0.jpg?VersionId=1v2bbMIJ1d7CMBs5E6WGpnbfPTsCTANU','Logistics','Negative',0,5,'2026-07-12 12:53:17','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(550,129,'Iran targets Gulf region after U.S. retaliatory airstrikes over Strait of Hormuz shipping attack','Tehran struck Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Oman and Jordan after Washington hit about 140 military-linked targets','The Globe and Mail','https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-iran-gulf-region-us-airstrikes-strait-of-hormuz/','https://www.theglobeandmail.com/resizer/v2/WYML3MC5JZGOBN5JNH6A7UGOZI.jpg?auth=ea43c2866a6407f5aa11b8cb4cef30a48ecfd9509f57dec31c1e9def9823273c&width=1200&height=800&quality=80&smart=true','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-12 07:00:02','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(551,129,'U.S., Iran intensify attacks over Strait of Hormuz','The United States launched several waves of strikes on Iran on Sunday over an Iranian attack on a container ship in the Strait of Hormuz that set it ablaze and left a crew member missing the day before. Iran responded with attacks on Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Jordan and Oman — the nation on the other side of the strait that Tehran has pressed to collaborate in managing shipping traffic.','CBC.ca','https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/iran-u-s-conflict-strait-july12-9.7267313','https://i.cbc.ca/ais/b1922ecc-79eb-4e6c-a992-a97b9f3b946a,1783893391823/full/max/0/default.jpg?im=Crop%2Crect%3D%280%2C0%2C3840%2C2160%29%3BResize%3D620','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-12 06:18:37','2026-07-14 04:09:38','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(552,123,'Global Times: Across the linked Tianshan Mountains, \'seeing China\' in Kyrgyzstan','Global Times: Kyrgyzstan sees growing China ties through trade, investment, and cultural exchange, with largely positive local views.','The Manila Times','https://www.manilatimes.net/2026/06/18/tmt-newswire/globenewswire/global-times-across-the-linked-tianshan-mountains-seeing-china-in-kyrgyzstan/2367901','https://manilatimes.net/manilatimes/uploads/images/2026/06/18/1103724.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-17 12:45:31','2026-07-14 04:10:50','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(553,123,'Across the linked Tianshan Mountains, \'seeing','Global Times: Kyrgyzstan sees growing China ties through trade, investment, and cultural exchange, with largely positive local views....','GlobeNewswire','https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/06/17/3313782/0/en/global-times-across-the-linked-tianshan-mountains-seeing-china-in-kyrgyzstan.html','https://newsroom.submitmypressrelease.com/system/media_files/images/000/072/921/original_jpeg/Picture1.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-17 12:42:57','2026-07-14 04:10:50','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(554,130,'Wombs for hire: the painful price of Asia’s baby trade','Commercial surrogacy is illegal in Thailand, Laos and Cambodia. It is also worth an estimated US$15 billion a year.','South China Morning Post','https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/people/article/3360160/wombs-hire-painful-price-asias-baby-trade','https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/styles/og_image_scmp_generic/public/d8/images/canvas/2026/07/10/48eb432d-1c43-4c31-b934-cd3e82b91d3e_780bab7d.jpg?itok=odPb81XH&v=1783682850','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-11 22:30:07','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(555,130,'Malaysia, Laos reaffirm commitment to expand trade, investment, connectivity','KUALA LUMPUR: Malaysia and Laos reaffirmed their commitment to deepening bilateral cooperation and strengthening their regional partnership by expanding collaboration in trade, investment and connectivity as the two countries marked the 60th anniversary of diplomatic relations.','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2026/07/05/malaysia-laos-reaffirm-commitment-to-expand-trade-investment-connectivity','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/07/05/3993723.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-05 05:55:00','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(556,130,'Putin Urges ASEAN to Expand Trade in National Currencies at Kazan Summit','Russian President Vladimir Putin on Thursday called for increased trade between Russia and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) using national currencies, according to remarks made at the conclusion of the two-day Russia-ASEAN summit in Kazan, Russia. The summit was attended by leaders from Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, […]','Natural News','https://www.naturalnews.com/2026-06-20-putin-urges-asean-expand-trade-in-national-currencies.html','https://www.naturalnews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/91/2026/06/putin-asean-national-currencies-2171-original.jpg','Trade','Positive',1,0,'2026-06-19 21:53:01','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(557,130,'Upgraded Highway 101 section in Nan opens','The Department of Highways has officially opened the upgraded section of Highway 101 in Nan, completing a major infrastructure project that will boost border connectivity, support economic growth, and establish trade and tourism links with Laos.','Bangkok Post','https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/3272469/upgraded-highway-101-section-in-nan-opens','https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20260618/c1_3272469_260618050439_700.jpg','Logistics','Positive',1,0,'2026-06-17 17:03:00','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(558,130,'Upgraded section in Nan opens','The Department of Highways (DOH) has officially opened the upgraded section of Highway No. 101 in Nan, completing a major infrastructure project that will boost border connectivity, support economic growth, and establish trade and tourism links with Laos.','Bangkok Post','https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/3272469/upgraded-section-in-nan-opens','https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20260618/c1_3272469_260618050439_700.jpg','Logistics','Positive',1,0,'2026-06-17 17:03:00','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(559,130,'Laos, Russia agree to expand cooperation','MOSCOW: Russia and Laos agreed to deepen cooperation on trade, technology, energy and people-to-people exchanges, at a meeting of the two countries\' prime ministers here Monday (June 15).','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/aseanplus/aseanplus-news/2026/06/16/laos-russia-agree-to-expand-cooperation','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/06/16/3960823.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-15 20:52:00','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(560,130,'Laos and Myanmar plan broader cooperation','VIENTIANE: Laos and Myanmar are forging ahead to deepen cooperation as their foreign ministers discussed plans for a bilateral meeting to boost collaboration on trade, investment, labour, energy, transport, border management and education.','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/aseanplus/aseanplus-news/2026/06/15/laos-and-myanmar-plan-broader-cooperation','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/06/15/3958958.png','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-14 22:33:00','2026-07-14 04:10:52','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(561,131,'US-Iran war: MoU ‘in crisis’! From Strait of Hormuz to Lebanon - key disputes threatening interim ceasefire explained','The US-Iran truce is collapsing, with Trump accusing Iran of ceasefire violations. Iran retaliates by blaming the US for disrupting shipping and violating the agreement. Tensions escalate as both sides disagree on the interpretation of key MoU provisions, impacting negotiations & regional security.','Livemint','https://www.livemint.com/news/world/usiran-war-mou-in-crisis-from-strait-of-hormuz-to-lebanon-key-disputes-threatening-interim-ceasefire-explained-11783956026417.html','https://www.livemint.com/lm-img/img/2026/07/13/1600x900/logo/UAE-IRAN-US-ISRAEL-WAR-0_1783958448806_1783958453406_d7ebf45f-fbab-4841-a7f3-db4451044a07.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,2,'2026-07-13 09:03:20','2026-07-14 04:10:57','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(562,131,'Israel-Lebanon Tensions & Middle East Crude Export Outlook','Explore how Israel–Lebanon tensions affect US–Iran deal prospects and Middle East Gulf crude export dynamics in the latest Strait Talk episode.','Argus Media','https://www.argusmedia.com/en/news-and-insights/video-insights/strait-talk-israel-lebanon-tensions-us-iran-deal-gulf-crude-exports','https://www.argusmedia.com/-/media/project/argusmedia/mainsite/images/14-generic-hero-banners/herobanner_1600x530_generic-c.jpg?h=530&iar=0&w=1600&rev=2cf023b4e0484c1bb091b9f72dbf7771&hash=72DBDFEBEF6EE62E751AB5DD2221C77E','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-09 17:00:00','2026-07-14 04:10:57','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(563,131,'US-Iran Peace Deal Live: Ship traffic through Hormuz surges as US-Iran ceasefire holds, says report','US-Iran War Live Updates: The United States and Iran are holding indirect technical talks in Qatar in a fresh diplomatic push to prevent another military escalation after weeks of conflict that rattled the Middle East. Discussions in Doha are centred on restoring commercial shipping through the Strait of Hormuz, securing a lasting ceasefire and implementing a 14-point interim accord signed last month, while broader negotiations on Iran\'s nuclear programme are expected to follow. US Vice President JD Vance said the talks were \"going well\" and stressed that President Donald Trump would not send American forces back into combat unless it became absolutely necessary. Trump also struck an optimistic tone, saying the \"denuclearization of Iran is moving along well\" and adding that Tehran had \"come a long way\" despite US forces having \"hit them very hard last week\". Iran, meanwhile, is pressing for international recognition of its authority over the Strait of Hormuz and the release of $6 billion in frozen assets, two of the main issues under discussion. Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Kazem Gharibabadi is leading Tehran\'s delegation, while Qatar and Pakistan are mediating the negotiations. Trump\'s son-in-law Jared Kushner and envoy Steve Witkoff helped prepare the talks through meetings with Qatari leaders but are not directly participating. The interim agreement also includes efforts to calm tensions in Lebanon, where parallel diplomatic talks continue alongside the US-Iran negotiations. Follow IndiaToday.in for the latest developments, key statements, diplomatic breakthroughs and regional reactions as events unfold.','India Today','https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/us-iran-peace-talks-qatar-live-updates-donald-trump-mojtaba-khamenei-agreement-lebanon-framework-strait-of-hormuz-middle-east-tensions-2938737-2026-07-02','https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/breaking_news/202607/iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-204324463-16x9.png?VersionId=k0QmebsFg3Zj.hlP.jcQyiyQgqAhBYnm','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-01 12:39:30','2026-07-14 04:10:57','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(564,131,'US-Iran peace talks face mid-August deadline amid Hormuz and Lebanon rifts','The United States and Iran are struggling to move beyond an interim truce as both sides dispute fresh talks and its terms. With rows over Hormuz shipping, sanctions and Lebanon unresolved, any permanent deal remains fragile.','India Today','https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/us-iran-talks-hormuz-dispute-lebanon-tensions-peace-deal-deadline-ptag-2937042-2026-06-30','https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/story/202606/pti-international-2-original_130-sixteen_nine.png?VersionId=AOmY7RhjJ2tE29U.kkjOxA5TvLa89325','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 12:26:37','2026-07-14 04:10:57','2026-07-16 10:09:17'),(565,131,'US-Iran War Highlights: Iran denies talks with US are scheduled in Qatar as White House to send envoys to Doha','US-Iran War News Live Updates: US and Iran trade strikes despite ceasefire as Hormuz tensions rise. Doha talks set for Tuesday amid Lebanon an