oday.in/world/story/china-myanmar-bangladesh-corridor-proposed-after-cpec-indias-east-pakistan-bri-indian-ocean-2938497-2026-07-02','https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/story/202607/during-talks-between-tarique-rahman-and-xi-jinping--bangladesh-agreed-to-develop-an-economic-zone-ne-011244978-16x9_0.png?VersionId=74MrCMZDsjevw1GPMTuDEYxudRxvh0Lk','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-01 20:41:55','2026-07-14 04:14:25','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(654,153,'Myanmar dam building backed by China','The halt of the project angered Beijing, but resentment at its deep influence in Myanmar and environmental concerns about flooding an area roughly the size of Singapore prevailed over plans to export 90 per cent of the 6 gigawatts of generated power to the giant neighbour','Telegraph India','https://www.telegraphindia.com/world/myanmars-new-government-to-restart-controversial-3-6-billion-dollar-dam-project-backed-by-china/cid/2168096','https://assets.telegraphindia.com/telegraph/2026/Jul/1782897342_myanmar.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-01 02:23:15','2026-07-14 04:14:25','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(655,153,'Xi backs Bangladesh in upholding sovereignty, \'rejecting foreign interference\' in talks with PM Rahman','Chinese President Xi Jinping pledged unwavering support for Bangladesh\'s sovereignty and rejection of foreign interference during Prime Minister Tarique Rahman\'s visit. Beijing also offered backing for Rahman\'s government and proposed a new economic corridor linking Bangladesh, Myanmar, and China. Discussions covered port modernization, a \'2+2 dialogue\' mechanism, and Mandarin\'s inclusion as a third language in Bangladesh\'s education system, with China welcoming Dhaka\'s potential BRICS membership.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/xi-backs-bangladesh-in-upholding-sovereignty-rejecting-foreign-interference-in-talks-with-pm-rahman/articleshow/132017558.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-132017558,