n a familiar face during free agency according to a new report.','MassLive','https://www.masslive.com/celtics/2026/06/celtics-interested-in-reunion-with-former-boston-guard-after-midseason-trade.html','https://www.masslive.com/resizer/v2/KSRA5WE7JFHLTJU6IWC2JCKKNI.jpg?auth=4f98aeae6699b10da6762ce67eadd6dcec57c3b645396e4cf1513abde723de32&width=1280&smart=true&quality=90','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 08:37:07','2026-07-14 04:19:14','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(818,194,'Russia’s Port Blitz Aims to Cripple Ukraine’s Western Lifeline, Seal its Ground Defeat','Supplies are being funneled from Europe to Ukraine\'s ports via Romania, which is why Russian strikes, including on Izmail, have been so relentless, retired Russian Navy Captain First Rank Vasily Dandykin tells Sputnik.','Sputnik News','https://sputnikglobe.com/20260713/russias-port-blitz-aims-to-cripple-ukraines-western-lifeline--seal-its-ground-defeat---expert--1124440018.html','https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/sharing/article/eng/1124440018.jpg?11211866621783947224','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-13 05:53:00','2026-07-14 04:19:16','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(819,194,'LEPAS L8 Sets Sail for Six European Countries - Expanding in the Global NEV Market with Elegance','WUHU, China, July 08, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Recently, a shipment ceremony for LEPAS - Chery Group\'s all-new NEV brand rooted in an elegant lifestyle - was held at Wuhu Port. Nearly 1,500 units of the LEPAS L8 PHEV were loaded and set sail, destined for multiple European countries including Italy, Spain, Greece, Croatia, Slovenia, and Romania. This large-scale vehicle shipment marks a substantial step forward in LEPAS\'s \'Year of Delivery\', honoring its global commitments with the power of elegance.','The Manila Times','https://www.manilatimes.net/2026/07/09/tmt-newswire/globenewswire/lepas-l8-sets-sail-for-six-european-countries-expanding-in-the-global-nev-market-with-elegance/2381316','https://manilatimes.net/manilatimes/uploads/images/2026/07/09/1130500.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-08 19:38:07','2026-07-14 04:19:16','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(820,194,'Romania detonates Russian drone fragments found near Ukraine border','BUCHAREST, June 30 - Romania\'s defence ministry said on Tuesday it safely detonated drone fragments found in the southeastern village of Rachelu, near the border with Ukraine, part of debris linked to a Russian attack on Ukrainian port infrastructure in April. Read more at straitstimes.com.','The Straits Times','https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/romania-detonates-russian-drone-fragments-found-near-ukraine-border','https://cassette.sphdigital.com.sg/image/straitstimes/c412ac9e70990554966027382c2121af66be4d0970fc489c8b9776ec9038262a','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 02:45:38','2026-07-14 04:19:16','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(821,194,'High-Stakes Demolition: Romanian Defense Dismantles Drone Threat','Romania\'s defense ministry successfully detonated fragments of a Russian drone near the southeastern village of Rachelu. The discovery is linked to an attack on Kyiv\'s port infrastructure. Romania, sharing a border with Ukraine, has experienced Russian drones breaching its airspace 15 times this year.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/law-order/3942840-high-stakes-demolition-romanian-defense-dismantles-drone-threat','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/25_07_2024_16_16_46_1411748.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-30 01:40:17','2026-07-14 04:19:16','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(822,194,'Romanian president nominates new candidate for prime minister','Romania\'s President Nicusor Dan has appointed Adrian Vestea as prime minister after independent candidate Eugen Tomac withdrew. Vestea, a liberal party member and Brasov county council president, will now attempt to form a political government to end a crisis that has impacted policymaking and the economy. He has 10 days to secure a parliamentary vote of confidence.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/romanian-president-nominates-new-candidate-for-prime-minister/articleshow/131717256.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-131717275,width-1200,height-630,imgsize-96232,overlay-economictimes/articleshow.jpg','Economy','Negative',0,1,'2026-06-14 00:32:00','2026-07-14 04:19:16','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(823,195,'Ukrainian drone strikes forced Russia to stop shipping in vital sea corridor','Ukraine’s drone blitz halted Russia’s Sea of Azov shipping in under a week.','Ars Technica','https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2026/07/ukrainian-drone-strikes-forced-russia-to-stop-shipping-in-vital-sea-corridor/','https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Russian-vessels-under-attack-Kerch-Strait-July-9-2026-1152x648.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-13 13:41:26','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(824,195,'Russia to bring flagship INNOPROM industrial fair to India in September','Russia\'s INNOPROM industrial trade fair will debut in India from September 9 to 11. This event aims to boost industrial cooperation and bilateral trade between the two nations. Key sectors for collaboration include pharmaceuticals, chemicals, and advanced manufacturing. Discussions are also underway for a bilateral investment protection treaty. India and Russia anticipate achieving $70 billion in bilateral trade this financial year.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/foreign-trade/russia-to-bring-flagship-innoprom-industrial-fair-to-india-in-september/articleshow/132375030.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-132375152,width-1200,height-630,imgsize-68606,overlay-economictimes/articleshow.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-13 11:32:00','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(825,195,'Russia’s Massive Strike on Gas Wells is the Price of Ukraine’s Drone War on Oil','The Russian Armed Forces had struck logistics centers and fuel, energy, and transport infrastructure used by Ukrainian forces, according to the Russian Ministry of Defense. The ministry reported on Thursday that Ukraine lost more than 450 soldiers in combat against Russia’s Battlegroup Vostok during the same period, in addition to losses on other fronts. [1] […]','Natural News','https://www.naturalnews.com/2026-07-13-russias-strike-gas-wells-ukraines-drone-war.html','https://www.naturalnews.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/91/2026/07/russian-armed-forces-logistics-centers-fuel-infrastructure-2627-original.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,2,'2026-07-13 10:46:45','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(826,195,'Grain Exports in Jeopardy: Ukraine-Russia Conflict Tightens Sea of Azov','Shipping restrictions in the Sea of Azov, following Ukrainian attacks, have disrupted Russian grain exports, a major global supplier. The curbs, not formally announced, impede entry and exit via the Kerch Strait, affecting market dynamics. If prolonged, these could significantly impact both global and domestic grain markets.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3949579-grain-exports-in-jeopardy-ukraine-russia-conflict-tightens-sea-of-azov','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/10_07_2025_12_32_09_1437056.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-13 07:00:03','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(827,195,'Sea of Azov Shipping Restrictions Raise Security Concerns, Impact Wheat Market','Shipping routes in the Sea of Azov have been restricted due to Ukrainian attacks on vessels, affecting Russia\'s grain exports, according to industry sources. The Kerch Strait remains closed, affecting the flow of wheat shipments. Russian authorities have not formally noted the curbs, sparking security discussions.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3949554-sea-of-azov-shipping-restrictions-raise-security-concerns-impact-wheat-market','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/25_09_2025_13_16_27_9165051.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-13 06:30:18','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(828,195,'Russia Developing Economy, Achieving New Results in Defense Industry - Putin','Russia is developing its economy, improving its armed forces and achieving new results in the defense industry, Russian President Vladimir Putin said on Monday.','Sputnik News','https://sputnikglobe.com/20260713/russia-developing-economy-achieving-new-results-in-defense-industry---putin-1124440482.html','https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/sharing/article/eng/1124440482.jpg?11244402511783948247','Economy','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-13 06:08:00','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(829,195,'Russia’s Port Blitz Aims to Cripple Ukraine’s Western Lifeline, Seal its Ground Defeat','Supplies are being funneled from Europe to Ukraine\'s ports via Romania, which is why Russian strikes, including on Izmail, have been so relentless, retired Russian Navy Captain First Rank Vasily Dandykin tells Sputnik.','Sputnik News','https://sputnikglobe.com/20260713/russias-port-blitz-aims-to-cripple-ukraines-western-lifeline--seal-its-ground-defeat---expert--1124440018.html','https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/sharing/article/eng/1124440018.jpg?11211866621783947224','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-13 05:53:00','2026-07-14 04:19:19','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(830,195,'Ukraine-Russia war latest: Kyiv bombs 15 more Russian ships on key trade route','Ukraine\'s attack also targeted Russian tankers and ferries near the Sea of Azov','The Independent','https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ukraine-russia-war-live-putin-trump-zelensky-drone-strikes-b3013631.html','https://static.independent.co.uk/2026/07/13/07/download.-1.?trim=0,0,0,0&width=1200&height=800&crop=1200:800','Trade','Negative',0,1,'2026