lves the Kenya Pipeline Company and Rwanda\'s Trade Ministry, as confirmed in official statements released on platform X.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3942748-kenya-and-rwanda-forge-path-for-fuel-import-framework','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/22_06_2024_13_30_27_2266721.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 22:30:01','2026-07-14 04:19:21','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(837,196,'Rwanda’s Export Challenge: IMF Urges Reforms to Unlock Growth and Cut Trade Gaps','The IMF finds that Rwanda’s export sector remains heavily dependent on a few commodities and markets, contributing to a persistent trade deficit of nearly 15% of GDP despite strong economic growth. The report urges investments in logistics, skills, private-sector development, and export diversification to improve competitiveness, strengthen external sustainability, and support Rwanda’s Vision 2050 development goals.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/business/3938465-rwandas-export-challenge-imf-urges-reforms-to-unlock-growth-and-cut-trade-gaps','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/22_06_2026_09_48_23_0229776.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Positive',4,0,'2026-06-22 01:01:56','2026-07-14 04:19:21','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(838,196,'Rwanda Seeks Sustainable Growth Path as IMF Supports Fiscal Adjustment Plan','Rwanda’s economy grew by a strong 9.4% in 2025, but rising inflation (13% in April 2026), elevated public debt (73.6% of GDP), and global uncertainties have prompted the IMF to approve a US$250 million support program focused on fiscal discipline, debt sustainability, and structural reforms. The report highlights the need for stronger domestic revenue mobilization, continued support from development partners, and greater private-sector participation to sustain growth, manage risks, and advance Rwanda’s long-term development goals.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/other/3934786-rwanda-seeks-sustainable-growth-path-as-imf-supports-fiscal-adjustment-plan','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/14_06_2026_13_49_44_3614007.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Positive',3,1,'2026-06-14 13:48:08','2026-07-14 04:19:21','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(839,197,'Indonesia sees new trade opportunities in Saudi Arabia\'s food security push','Indonesia sees new trade opportunities in Saudi Arabia\'s food security push-','Xinhua','https://english.news.cn/20260716/15e6ddaa81164538969db89fad3759ba/c.html',NULL,'Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 17:00:00','2026-07-16 09:52:52','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(840,197,'Explainer-Who are the Houthis, Iran’s allies in Yemen?','July 15 (Reuters) - Yemen\'s Houthi movement fired missiles at Saudi Arabia after accusing the kingdom of bombing an airport under their control on Monday,breaking a four-year truce in the conflict between the kingdom and the Iran-aligned group.The move signals the end of a period of de-escalation and raises concerns that Iran could now start using its Houthi allies to close the Bab el-Mandeb gateway to the Red Sea, which would be the second global shipping choke point disrupted after the Strait of Hormuz.WHO ARE THE HOUTHIS?','Al-Monitor','https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2026/03/explainer-who-are-houthis-irans-allies-yemen','https://www.al-monitor.com/sites/default/files/styles/social_media_share/public/2026-03/2026-03-13T112148Z_2_LYNXMPEM2C0MY_RTROPTP_4_IRAN-CRISIS-YEMEN-HOUTHIS.JPG?h=278c4d67&itok=dhIDB4gQ','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 03:17:36','2026-07-16 09:52:52','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(841,197,'Houthi Missiles Signal a New Phase in Middle Eastern Tensions','The Houthi movement in Yemen fired missiles at Saudi Arabia, ending a four-year truce. This escalation could threaten global shipping lanes. The Houthis, a military, political, and religious group based in northern Yemen, have continued to strengthen ties with Iran, complicating regional geopolitics and international commerce.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/politics/3950540-houthi-missiles-signal-a-new-phase-in-middle-eastern-tensions','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/25_06_2024_21_27_13_7271003.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 01:50:34','2026-07-16 09:52:52','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(842,197,'Houthis Under Scanner: UNSC To Monitor Red Sea For Six More Months Amid Iran War','The UN Security Council has extended monitoring of Houthi attacks in the Red Sea for six months as Yemen\'s Iran-backed Houthis resume missile attacks on Saudi Arabia, raising fresh concerns over maritime security and global shipping through the Bab el-Mandeb Strait., Middle East, Times Now','Times Now','https://www.timesnownews.com/world/middle-east/houthis-under-scanner-unsc-to-monitor-red-sea-for-six-more-months-amid-iran-war-article-155103378','https://images.timesnownews.com/thumb/msid-155103490,thumbsize-1104813,width-1280,height-720,resizemode-75/155103490.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-15 00:03:02','2026-07-16 09:52:52','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(843,197,'Crude shipments from Saudi Arabia\'s Yanbu port near maximum levels amid Houthi tensions','Saudi Arabia is maximizing oil exports through its Yanbu port this week. Increased loadings at Yanbu reflect rising tensions with Yemen\'s Houthi militia. The kingdom is also considering pipeline expansion to bypass the Strait of Hormuz. Shipments from Yanbu have averaged over four million barrels daily recently. Concerns exist that Yanbu could become a Houthi target following prior attacks.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/energy/oil-gas/crude-shipments-from-saudi-arabias-yanbu-port-near-maximum-levels-amid-houthi-tensions/articleshow/132406414.cms','ht