7-16 10:09:18'),(858,219,'Seychelles invites Indian businesses to tap gateway to Africa after PM Modi\'s visit: Envoy','Seychelles has invited Indian businesses to leverage the island nation\'s strategic location as a gateway to Africa following Prime Minister Narendra Modi\'s recent state visit, as the two countries seek to strengthen bilateral ties and ramp up trade and commerce, Harisoa Lalatiana Accouche, High Commissioner of Seychelles to India, said on Saturday.','The Tribune','https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/business/seychelles-invites-indian-businesses-to-tap-gateway-to-africa-after-pm-modis-visit-envoy/','https://www.tribuneindia.com/sortd-service/imaginary/v22-01/jpg/large/high?url=dGhldHJpYnVuZS1zb3J0ZC1wcm8tcHJvZC1zb3J0ZC9tZWRpYTVhYTc0N2QwLTc3OTktMTFmMS1hZmFlLTJkNzNlMTMwYzExYi5qcGc=','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-04 04:13:09','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(859,219,'DC Edit | India, Seychelles Bond Stronger','Mr Modi’s assurance on behalf of India that the partnership is not to be defined by size is a telling comment that should have pleased Seychelles whose aspirations to build a sustainable Blue Economy remain high. Along with the pledge also comes umbrella aid and an economic package of $175 million plus crucial materials like cement and rice','Deccan Chronicle','https://www.deccanchronicle.com/opinion/dc-comment/dc-edit-india-seychelles-bond-stronger-1967146','https://www.deccanchronicle.com/h-upload/2026/06/29/2058033-untitled-design-4.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 10:02:19','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(860,219,'PM Narendra Modi says \"Chutney and Samosa reflect the shared heritage of India and Seychelles\": 6 traditional dishes that prove it','Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s state visit to Seychelles is focused on celebrating 50 years of bilateral diplomatic relations and boosting maritime security. On Sunday, highlightig the deep cultural and people-to-people ties between India and Seychelles, he said that the shared culinary traditions such as chutney and samosa reflect the enduring bond between the two nations. Addressing the gathering, he said, “Chutney and samosa flavours are among the unique elements that reflect the shared heritage of India and Seychelles.\" In his remarks, he stressed that the flavours of chutney and samosa have become symbols of the historical and cultural links that connect the Indian diaspora with the island nation. He noted that the Indian community has made significant contributions to Seychelles over the years while preserving traditions that continue to strengthen bilateral ties. According to food experts, while both the countries are separated by thousands of kilometres, India and Seychelles share a rich culinary connection shaped by centuries of trade, migration, and cultural exchange. Take a look at these six Indian and Seychellois dishes that showcase this fascinating culinary overlap.','Times of India','https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/food-news/pm-narendra-modi-says-chutney-and-samosa-reflect-the-shared-heritage-of-india-and-seychelles-6-traditional-dishes-that-prove-it/photostory/132070920.cms','https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-132070937,width-1280,height-720,imgsize-28964,resizemode-6,overlay-toi_sw,pt-32,y_pad-600/photo.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 04:20:51','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(861,219,'Modi and Seychelles team up for blue economy and climate aid','PM Modi\'s historic visit addresses the unique climate vulnerabilities of the archipelago while securing strategic sea lanes of communication.','ThePrint','https://theprint.in/opinion/forthwrite/modi-seychelles-indian-ocean-climate-aid-blue-economy/2972471/','https://staticprintenglish.theprint.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Modi-tortoise.png','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-29 02:41:25','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(862,219,'Seychelles leaders hail PM Modi\'s visit, push for deeper ties with India across key sectors','Lawmakers highlight five decades of bilateral relations, calling for stronger cooperation in maritime security, climate resilience, tourism, culture, innovation and the blue economy.','ThePrint','https://theprint.in/world/seychelles-leaders-hail-pm-modis-visit-push-for-deeper-ties-with-india-across-key-sectors/2972294/','https://staticprintenglish.theprint.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ANI-20260629020212-e1782704312210.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-28 20:40:10','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(863,219,'Indian ocean an \'ocean of opportunity\': Modi','Prime Minister Narendra Modi underscored the inseparable security and defense ties between India and Seychelles, highlighting new avenues for industrial cooperation. He emphasized India\'s vision for the Indian Ocean as an \'Ocean of Opportunity.\' Discussions focused on strengthening maritime security, digital connectivity via UPI, and collaboration in the blue economy, including clean energy and space exploration, reinforcing decades of close partnership.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/india/indian-ocean-an-ocean-of-opportunity-modi/articleshow/132057751.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-132057827,width-1200,height-630,imgsize-92590,overlay-economictimes/articleshow.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-28 11:49:00','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(864,219,'India and Seychelles: A key maritime partnership','PM Modi’s Seychelles visit strengthens India’s trade & security interests in the Western Indian Ocean','Hindustan Times','https://www.hindustantimes.com/editorials/india-and-seychelles-a-key-maritime-partnership-101782666030897.html','https://www.hindustantimes.com/ht-img/img/2026/06/28/550x309/India-s-support-helps-Seychelles-monitor-its-vast-_1782666028896.jpg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-28 10:00:30','2026-07-16 09:53:02','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(865,205,'Low-cost AI could transform health care logistics in low- and middle-income countries','Managing a medical supply chain in low- and middle-income countries can mean navigating a landscape prone to extreme and unexpected disruptions. In Sierra Leone, for instance, external forces ranging from an attempted military coup and an infectious disease outbreak to a widespread electricity outage can complicate public health logistics.','Medical Xpress','https://medicalxpress.com/news/2026-06-ai-health-logistics-middle-income.html','https://scx2.b-cdn.net/gfx/news/hires/2026/transforming-health-ca.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-23 09:40:05','2026-07-16 09:53:06','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(866,200,'Marcos returns with Singapore pledges','Marcos returns from Singapore with commitments to boost trade, AI, digital infrastructure and healthcare cooperation.','SunStar Philippines','https://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/marcos-returns-with-singapore-pledges','https://cf-images.assettype.com/sunstar%2F2026-07-16%2Fsyzv3ns1%2FUntitled-design-16.png?w=1200&ar=40%3A21&auto=format%2Ccompress&ogImage=true&mode=crop&enlarge=true&overlay=false&overlay_position=bottom&overlay_width=100','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 21:54:15','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(867,200,'Fewer vessels travel through Hormuz as US, Iran continue strikes','SINGAPORE, July 16 (Reuters) - Fewer vessels travelled through the Strait of Hormuz on Wednesday, the first day after the U.S. reimposed its naval blockade on Iranian ports with both countries escalating strikes across the Gulf, shipping data showed.Seven vessels crossed the strait on Wednesday, mostly on the Iranian route, down from 13 the previous day, Kpler data showed.','Al-Monitor','https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2026/07/fewer-vessels-travel-through-hormuz-us-iran-continue-strikes','https://www.al-monitor.com/sites/default/files/styles/social_media_share/public/2026-07/2026-07-16T023119Z_2_LYNXMPEM6F02X_RTROPTP_4_IRAN-CRISIS-OMAN-HORMUZ.JPG?h=7e5ae70f&itok=6Jvpm3n4','Logistics','Negative',0,2,'2026-07-15 19:31:19','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(868,200,'China\'s Q2 economic growth cools to 3-1/2-year low as imbalances worsen','BEIJING/SINGAPORE: China\'s economy expanded at its slowest pace in over three years in the second quarter, with weak household consumption clouding strong manufacturing and exports and intensifying concerns over the long-term sustainability of its unbalanced growth model.','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/business/business-news/2026/07/15/china039s-q2-economic-growth-cools-to-3-12-year-low-as-imbalances-worsen','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/07/15/4011917.png','Logistics','Positive',3,0,'2026-07-15 00:33:00','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(869,200,'Iran-linked vessels pass through Hormuz ahead of US blockade','SINGAPORE, July 15 (Reuters) - The ⁠number of vessels transiting through the Strait of Hormuz ticked up on Tuesday, ⁠with most of them linked to Iranian trade, before a U.S. blockade took effect ‌on Wednesday, shipping data showed.','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2026/07/15/iran-linked-vessels-pass-through-hormuz-ahead-of-us-blockade','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/07/15/4011376.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 20:22:00','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(870,200,'[In This Economy] Why Singapore moves while Metro Manila doesn’t','Singapore’s exemplary rail system did not spring from wealth alone. Instead, it sprang from meticulous planning and continuity.','Rappler','https://www.rappler.com/voices/thought-leaders/in-this-economy-why-singapore-transport-system-moves-metro-manila-trains-behind/','https://www.rappler.com/tachyon/2026/07/SINGAPORE-TRAINS-VS-MM-JUL-15-2026.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 19:39:01','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(871,200,'Analysts expect full-year GDP at 4.3%, higher than earlier estimates','Analysts expect this year\'s GDP to come in at 4.3 per cent, on the back of an AI-related manufacturing boom. This is higher than the earlier estimate of a two to four per cent growth for the full year. The optimism comes after Singapore\'s economy grew by 5.7 per cent in the second quarter. The manufacturing cluster was','CNA','https://www.channelnewsasia.com/watch/analysts-expect-full-year-gdp-43-higher-earlier-estimates-6253831','https://dam.mediacorp.sg/image/upload/s--OSRa7cVG--/c_fill,g_auto,h_676,w_1200/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mediacorp/cna/image/2026/07/14/img_20260714_223642_3497_0.jpg?itok=nknh496z','Economy','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-14 07:39:56','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(872,200,'Singapore records strong 5.7% economic growth in second quarter','Singapore\'s economy grew 5.7% in the second quarter, beating market expectations, mainly due to strong growth in the manufacturing sector.','BOL News','https://www.bolnews.com/business/singapore-records-strong-5-7-economic-growth-in-second-quarter/','https://www.bolnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Singapore.webp','Economy','Positive',4,0,'2026-07-14 05:20:33','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(873,200,'Asia markets choppy as threat of Trump Hormuz levy spooks traders','SINGAPORE: Stocks swung between gains and losses and oil hit a one-month high in early Asian trading on Tuesday after President Donald Trump said the U.S. was reinstating its blockade of Iranian shipping in the Gulf and would collect a 20% fee on cargo traversing the Strait of Hormuz.','The Star','https://www.thestar.com.my/business/2026/07/14/asia-markets-choppy-as-threat-of-trump-hormuz-levy-spooks-traders','https://apicms.thestar.com.my/uploads/images/2026/07/14/4009129.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-13 19:08:00','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(874,200,'Singapore GDP growth slows to 5.7% in Q2 despite AI export boom as Middle East tensions weigh','Gross domestic product grew 5.7% in the second quarter from the previous year, based on advance estimates released by the Ministry of Trade and Industry on Tuesday.','Moneycontrol','https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/singapore-gdp-growth-slows-to-5-7-in-q2-despite-ai-export-boom-as-middle-east-tensions-weigh-13973042.html','https://images.moneycontrol.com/static-mcnews/2024/12/20241206060447_3-singapore.jpg','Logistics','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-13 18:43:50','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(875,200,'Singapore\'s Q2 economic growth slows to 5.7%','Singapore\'s economy grew 5.7% in Q2 2026, slowing from Q1 due to eased expansion in construction and trade, despite AI manufacturing strength. Read more at straitstimes.com.','The Straits Times','https://www.straitstimes.com/business/singapores-second-quarter-growth-eases-to-5-7-as-iran-war-tempers-ai-powered-manufacturing-growth','https://cassette.sphdigital.com.sg/image/straitstimes/41835649b481a9360618f0258c7f5712991a6f806a4c440a33b1a340442e0ea9','Trade','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-13 17:32:50','2026-07-16 09:54:28','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(876,214,'New US sanctions bill targets big 5 buyers of Russian crude. What are the repercussions for India','Top 5 purchasers ​of Russian crude are China, India, Slovakia, Hungary & Azerbaijan. The bill proposes exemptions for countries that import less than 15% of their natural gas from Russia.','ThePrint','https://theprint.in/economy/new-us-sanctions-bill-targets-big-5-buyers-of-russian-crude-what-are-the-repercussions-for-india/2987037/','https://staticprintenglish.theprint.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Untitled-design-63-1.png','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 03:14:10','2026-07-16 09:54:32','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(877,214,'PM Modi Lands in Geneva for G7 Summit Following Historic Slovakia Visit','Prime Minister Narendra Modi arrived in Geneva for the G7 Summit after a historic and productive visit to Slovakia. The involvement at G7 will be his seventh in a row, and during his Slovakia visit, he received the prestigious Order of the White Double Cross from President Pellegrini. Key agreements were reached to strengthen India-Slovakia ties, focusing on education, talent mobility, and trade.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/international/3935742-pm-modi-lands-in-geneva-for-g7-summit-following-historic-slovakia-visit','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/16_06_2026_15_12_18_4319611.jpg&width=920&format=jpeg','Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-16 02:42:22','2026-07-16 09:54:32','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(878,214,'PM Modi Discusses ‘Growing Partnership’ With Slovakian President','Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Slovak President Peter Pellegrini discuss a growing India-Slovakia partnership in digitalisation, innovation, defence, nuclear energy and trade in Bratislava, highlighting new agreements, investment opportunities, people-to-people ties and cooperation on technology, green energy and AI.','Outlook India','https://www.outlookindia.com/international/pm-modi-discusses-growing-partnership-with-slovakian-president-2','https://cf-images.assettype.com/outlookindia/2026-06-16/dh0ztdtb/ModiPTI.jpg?w=1200&ar=40%3A21&auto=format%2Ccompress&ogImage=true&mode=crop&enlarge=true&overlay=false&overlay_position=bottom&overlay_width=100','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-16 01:36:06','2026-07-16 09:54:32','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(879,215,'LEPAS L8 Sets Sail for Six European Countries - Expanding in the Global NEV Market with Elegance','WUHU, China, July 08, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Recently, a shipment ceremony for LEPAS - Chery Group\'s all-new NEV brand rooted in an elegant lifestyle - was held at Wuhu Port. Nearly 1,500 units of the LEPAS L8 PHEV were loaded and set sail, destined for multiple European countries including Italy, Spain, Greece, Croatia, Slovenia, and Romania. This large-scale vehicle shipment marks a substantial step forward in LEPAS\'s \'Year of Delivery\', honoring its global commitments with the power of elegance.','The Manila Times','https://www.manilatimes.net/2026/07/09/tmt-newswire/globenewswire/lepas-l8-sets-sail-for-six-european-countries-expanding-in-the-global-nev-market-with-elegance/2381316','https://manilatimes.net/manilatimes/uploads/images/2026/07/09/1130500.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-08 19:38:07','2026-07-16 09:54:35','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(880,208,'US Move to Withdraw Support Sparks Concerns for Somalia\'s Peace Mission','The U.S. plans to stop supporting the African Union\'s peacekeeping mission in Somalia beyond this year, jeopardizing its operations. The mission is crucial in backing Somalia\'s government against al-Shabaab militants, but relies heavily on U.N. support for essential logistics and funding, which is now at risk.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/law-order/3944430-us-move-to-withdraw-support-sparks-concerns-for-somalias-peace-mission','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/28_06_2025_12_13_14_5139491.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-02 12:38:14','2026-07-16 09:54:40','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(881,208,'U.S. Withdrawal Challenges Stability of AU Mission in Somalia','The United States plans to halt support for the AU\'s peacekeeping mission in Somalia starting next year. The AU mission, heavily dependent on U.N. logistics, helps counter al-Shabaab but faces operational challenges and funding cuts as Washington ceases aid, drawing concern over Somalia\'s future stability.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/law-order/3944392-us-withdrawal-challenges-stability-of-au-mission-in-somalia','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/imagegallery/27_05_2019_11_52_07_9391333.jpg&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-02 10:39:40','2026-07-16 09:54:40','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(882,252,'Amazon will launch its satellite internet in South Africa, seemingly beating Musk in his homeland','Amazon said Wednesday that the technology company will launch its new satellite internet service Amazon Leo in South Africa in 2027, seemingly pushing ahead of Elon Musk’s rival Starlink to win business in Africa’s most advanced economy.','NBC News','https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/amazon-launch-satellite-internet-south-africa-rcna587679','https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_nbcnews-fp-1200-630,f_auto,q_auto:best/rockcms/2026-05/260520-Jeff-Bezos-ch-1046-994054.jpg','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 09:52:38','2026-07-16 09:54:43','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(883,252,'Amazon will launch its satellite internet in South Africa, seemingly beating Musk in his homeland','Amazon says that the technology company will launch its new satellite internet service Amazon Leo in South Africa in 2027. That appears to put the company owned by Jeff Bezos ahead of Elon Musk’s rival Starlink to claim business in Africa’s most advanced economy. South Africa is also Musk\'s homeland. Amazon said Wednesday that it would partner with South African internet provider Herotel in its first agreement to provide satellite internet in Africa. Amazon’s announcement follows Musk’s bitter criticism of his country of birth. The world’s richest man has said South African affirmative action regulations have prevented him from launching Starlink there because he\'s white.','The Atlanta Journal-Constitution','https://www.ajc.com/news/2026/07/amazon-to-launch-its-satellite-internet-in-south-africa-seemingly-beating-out-musk-in-his-homeland/','https://images.ajc.com/resizer/v2/GD4NTY5UTFA27AL3VWN3NZB37U.jpg?auth=d5edd82d3b38fe4fd57a8233a4c7d94527d3cdeb3d4422dbfb1915268fce8c90&width=1200&height=630&smart=true','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 09:31:46','2026-07-16 09:54:43','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(884,252,'Amazon to beat Starlink launching satellite internet in South Africa','Amazon said it will launch its new satellite internet service in South Africa in 2027, advancing Elon Musk\'s Starlink in Africa’s most advanced economy.','Bnn Bloomberg','https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/company-news/2026/07/15/amazon-to-launch-its-satellite-internet-in-south-africa-seemingly-beating-out-musk-in-his-homeland/','https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/resizer/v2/JA52BTMMCLLDQLGOJZQKKUV4VE.jpg?smart=true&auth=5e67291a9c08b2ec317daa8721cb8529630a48ddef58390ec2cdda56d7b6bb95&width=1200&height=630','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 08:37:17','2026-07-16 09:54:43','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(885,252,'Amazon to beat Starlink launching satellite internet in South Africa','Amazon said it will launch its new satellite internet service in South Africa in 2027, advancing Elon Musk\'s Starlink in Africa’s most advanced economy.','CP24 Toronto','https://www.cp24.com/news/world/2026/07/15/amazon-to-launch-its-satellite-internet-in-south-africa-seemingly-beating-out-musk-in-his-homeland/','https://www.cp24.com/resizer/v2/JA52BTMMCLLDQLGOJZQKKUV4VE.jpg?smart=true&auth=5e67291a9c08b2ec317daa8721cb8529630a48ddef58390ec2cdda56d7b6bb95&width=1200&height=630','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 08:37:17','2026-07-16 09:54:43','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(886,252,'China, South Africa textile trade show opens in Cape Town, boosting bilateral industry cooperation','China, South Africa textile trade show opens in Cape Town, boosting bilateral industry cooperation-','Xinhua','https://english.news.cn/20260715/fdd28bbf50d44d8db8c6de3b340fa3c7/c.html',NULL,'Trade','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 17:00:00','2026-07-16 09:54:43','2026-07-16 10:09:18'),(887,252,'Deputy Minister Calls for Stronger Action Against Illegal Fishing Trade','According to Singh, protecting South Africa\'s coastal and marine resources requires coordinated action from every part of the justice system.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/law-order/3950048-deputy-minister-calls-for-stronger-action-against-illegal-fishing-trade','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/19_05_2025_21_36_26_957196.jfif&width=920