Modi As Boat Carrying Indian Tourists Capsizes Near Vietnam\'s Phu Quoc Island','A tourist boat capsized near Phu Quoc Island in Vietnam on Saturday, July 11. The tourist speedboat carrying 32 Indian tourists and four crew members capsized near Phu Quoc Island while returning to An Thoi Port. 15 Indians were killed in the incident, local media reported; however, an official confirmation is awaited. , India News News, Times Now','Times Now','https://www.timesnownews.com/india/vietnam-boat-tragedy-live-updates-indian-tourists-speedboat-capsize-phu-quoc-rescue-operation-latest-news-indian-embassy-liveblog-155076505','https://images.timesnownews.com/thumb/msid-155076505,thumbsize-2512167,width-1280,height-720,resizemode-75/155076505.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-11 05:55:57','2026-07-16 10:08:16','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1092,251,'Explainer-Why Iranian, Houthi threats to Red Sea shipping matter more for oil now','July 15 (Reuters) - Iran has warned that its campaign to throttle global energy markets could be expanded from the Strait of Hormuz to the vital Red Sea route if U.S. attacks continue, a threat that depends on its Houthi allies in Yemen.This is why it matters and what it means for the Iran war and the global energy crisis:HOW BIG IS THE RISK TO GLOBAL ENERGY MARKETS?Closure of the Bab el-Mandeb strait — gateway to the Red Sea — would open a new front in the energy crisis and Iran\'s overarching conflict with the U.S.','Al-Monitor','https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2026/06/explainer-why-iranian-houthi-threats-red-sea-shipping-matter-more-oil-now','https://www.al-monitor.com/sites/default/files/styles/social_media_share/public/2026-06/2026-06-08T115736Z_1_LYNXMPEM570UU_RTROPTP_4_IRAN-CRISIS-LEBANON-YEMEN.JPG?h=790be497&itok=kPxU6Mqz','Logistics','Negative',0,3,'2026-07-15 05:33:54','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1093,251,'Explainer-Who are the Houthis, Iran’s allies in Yemen?','July 15 (Reuters) - Yemen\'s Houthi movement fired missiles at Saudi Arabia after accusing the kingdom of bombing an airport under their control on Monday,breaking a four-year truce in the conflict between the kingdom and the Iran-aligned group.The move signals the end of a period of de-escalation and raises concerns that Iran could now start using its Houthi allies to close the Bab el-Mandeb gateway to the Red Sea, which would be the second global shipping choke point disrupted after the Strait of Hormuz.WHO ARE THE HOUTHIS?','Al-Monitor','https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2026/03/explainer-who-are-houthis-irans-allies-yemen','https://www.al-monitor.com/sites/default/files/styles/social_media_share/public/2026-03/2026-03-13T112148Z_2_LYNXMPEM2C0MY_RTROPTP_4_IRAN-CRISIS-YEMEN-HOUTHIS.JPG?h=278c4d67&itok=dhIDB4gQ','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 03:17:36','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1094,251,'Houthi Missiles Signal a New Phase in Middle Eastern Tensions','The Houthi movement in Yemen fired missiles at Saudi Arabia, ending a four-year truce. This escalation could threaten global shipping lanes. The Houthis, a military, political, and religious group based in northern Yemen, have continued to strengthen ties with Iran, complicating regional geopolitics and international commerce.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/politics/3950540-houthi-missiles-signal-a-new-phase-in-middle-eastern-tensions','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/25_06_2024_21_27_13_7271003.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-15 01:50:34','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1095,251,'Houthis Under Scanner: UNSC To Monitor Red Sea For Six More Months Amid Iran War','The UN Security Council has extended monitoring of Houthi attacks in the Red Sea for six months as Yemen\'s Iran-backed Houthis resume missile attacks on Saudi Arabia, raising fresh concerns over maritime security and global shipping through the Bab el-Mandeb Strait., Middle East, Times Now','Times Now','https://www.timesnownews.com/world/middle-east/houthis-under-scanner-unsc-to-monitor-red-sea-for-six-more-months-amid-iran-war-article-155103378','https://images.timesnownews.com/thumb/msid-155103490,thumbsize-1104813,width-1280,height-720,resizemode-75/155103490.jpg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-15 00:03:02','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1096,251,'Tensions Rise as Iran Threatens Energy Corridors Amid U.S. Naval Blockade','Iran\'s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps threatens to close vital energy corridors following the U.S. naval blockade. With potential Houthi support in Yemen, key global shipping routes are endangered, escalating tensions. U.S. strikes and Trump\'s economic threats exacerbate the situation, causing global oil prices to rise.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/science-environment/3950456-tensions-rise-as-iran-threatens-energy-corridors-amid-us-naval-blockade','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/aiimagegallery/08_07_2024_14_06_18_7731956.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Negative',0,1,'2026-07-14 21:56:15','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1097,251,'Crude shipments from Saudi Arabia\'s Yanbu port near maximum levels amid Houthi tensions','Saudi Arabia is maximizing oil exports through its Yanbu port this week. Increased loadings at Yanbu reflect rising tensions with Yemen\'s Houthi militia. The kingdom is also considering pipeline expansion to bypass the Strait of Hormuz. Shipments from Yanbu have averaged over four million barrels daily recently. Concerns exist that Yanbu could become a Houthi target following prior attacks.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/energy/oil-gas/crude-shipments-from-saudi-arabias-yanbu-port-near-maximum-levels-amid-houthi-tensions/articleshow/132406414.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-132406414,width-1200,height-630,imgsize-9648,overlay-economictimes/articleshow.jpg','Logistics','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-14 21:41:00','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1098,251,'One misstep away: Pakistan’s Iran tightrope faces its toughest test','Saudi Arabia and Yemen\'s Houthi movement are facing renewed conflict, raising regional escalation fears and making Pakistan\'s strategic balance between Saudi Arabia and Iran more difficult. A recent Saudi-Pakistan defence pact has added more complexity to Islamabad\'s obligations. The Bab el-Mandeb Strait\'s importance has grown as shipping disruptions have become a bigger concern.','The Economic Times','https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/one-misstep-away-pakistans-iran-tightrope-faces-its-toughest-test/articleshow/132394903.cms','https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-132396044,width-1200,height-630,imgsize-40322,overlay-etdefence/articleshow.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 11:31:00','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1099,251,'Tensions Surge: Saudi Arabia\'s Yanbu Port Faces Increased Crude Loadings Amid Yemen Conflict','Saudi Arabia\'s Yanbu port, a key oil export hub, is operating at near maximum capacity as tensions with Yemen\'s Houthi militia escalate. The kingdom aims to boost exports amid regional conflicts, particularly with Iran. Industry sources reveal possible expansions and concerns of potential Houthi attacks on Yanbu.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/science-environment/3950235-tensions-surge-saudi-arabias-yanbu-port-faces-increased-crude-loadings-amid-yemen-conflict','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/imagegallery/27_06_2019_18_00_51_6514463.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Positive',1,0,'2026-07-14 08:55:26','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1100,251,'Red Sea could soon be more dangerous than Strait of Hormuz: Why Yemen is becoming the new flashpoint','As tensions spread to Yemen, the Bab el-Mandeb Strait is emerging as another critical maritime chokepoint alongside Hormuz. Any disruption in the Red Sea could hit global shipping, energy supplies and oil prices.','Moneycontrol','https://www.moneycontrol.com/world/red-sea-could-soon-be-more-dangerous-than-strait-of-hormuz-why-yemen-is-becoming-the-new-flashpoint-article-13973868.html','https://images.moneycontrol.com/static-mcnews/2026/07/20260714143339_Bab-El-Mandeb-2.jpg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 07:33:52','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1101,251,'After Hormuz, Iran turns to Red Sea gateway as new pressure point','BEIRUT, July 14 - Having choked off shipping through the Strait of Hormuz, Iran is now signaling it could play its most dangerous card yet: using Yemen\'s Houthi allies to shut the Bab el-Mandeb gateway to the Red Sea, opening a new front against Washington and putting two of the world\'s most vital energy arteries at risk. Read more at straitstimes.com.','The Straits Times','https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/after-hormuz-iran-turns-to-red-sea-gateway-as-new-pressure-point','https://cassette.sphdigital.com.sg/image/straitstimes/a62870a58f981598c3cfe8864c370703d443b8816a6c3915d3f59a2d028b81f0','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-14 07:20:39','2026-07-16 10:08:24','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1102,253,'Socioeconomic and ecological drivers of contagious pig diseases in free-range systems: Evidence from Gwembe Valley, Zambia','Author summary Free-range pig farming is common in rural Zambia and helps many families earn income and improve food security. However, when pigs roam freely, they can easily come into contact with waste, other animals, and informal markets, which increases the risk of disease spread. Two important diseases in such systems are African swine fever, which kills pigs and affects farmers’ livelihoods, and porcine cysticercosis, which can also infect people and is linked to poor sanitation. We worked with farmers, traders, transporters, and veterinary staff in Gwembe District to understand how everyday practices, environment, and trade patterns influence disease risks. Instead of focusing only on biology, we looked at how non-biological realities shape pig management. Participants showed that poverty, limited veterinary services, seasonal water shortages, and informal pig trade all contribute to disease risk. They also highlighted gaps in disease awareness and reporting. Our findings suggest that improving pig health is not only about medicines. Better sanitation, simple pig housing, farmer education, and community-based surveillance can reduce disease risks while fitting local livelihoods. This study shows that locally informed, participatory approaches can support healthier pigs, safer food, and more resilient rural communities.','PLOS (Public Library of Science)','https://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pntd.0014523','https://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article/figure/image?id=10.1371/journal.pntd.0014523.g004&size=inline','Logistics','Positive',3,0,'2026-07-08 17:00:00','2026-07-16 10:08:26','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1103,253,'AEON Expands to Zambia, Bridging Global Crypto and Agentic Commerce with Local Mobile Money','/PRNewswire/ -- AEON, the settlement layer for the agentic economy, has expanded AEON Pay into Zambia, integrating local wallets Airtel Money and MTN Mobile...','PR Newswire UK','https://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/aeon-expands-to-zambia-bridging-global-crypto-and-agentic-commerce-with-local-mobile-money-302815581.html','https://www.prnewswire.co.uk/content/dam/prnewswire/icons/2019-Q4-PRN-Icon-32-32.png','Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-01 00:57:00','2026-07-16 10:08:26','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1104,253,'Zambia\'s economy grows by 7.7 pct in Q1 2026','Zambia\'s economy grows by 7.7 pct in Q1 2026-','Xinhua','https://english.news.cn/20260625/54fb926babb24db9839d3d7b17c8d958/c.html',NULL,'Economy','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-24 17:00:00','2026-07-16 10:08:26','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1105,254,'Zimbabwe\'s trade promotion body hails blueberry exports to China under new trade deal','Zimbabwe\'s trade promotion body hails blueberry exports to China under new trade deal-','Xinhua','https://english.news.cn/20260710/5d7385c748874965840585e92d558f14/c.html',NULL,'Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-07-09 17:00:00','2026-07-16 10:08:29','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1106,254,'Limpopo, Zimbabwe Sign Trade Pact to Boost Business Links','The newly signed Memorandum of Understanding provides a framework for closer collaboration between LEDA and ZimTrade in promoting trade and supporting businesses seeking opportunities across the border.','Devdiscourse','https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/law-order/3940894-limpopo-zimbabwe-sign-trade-pact-to-boost-business-links','https://www.devdiscourse.com/img?imageUrl=https://devdiscourse.blob.core.windows.net/devnews/25_06_2026_21_37_33_8774405.png&width=920&format=jpeg','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-25 09:13:06','2026-07-16 10:08:29','2026-07-16 10:09:19'),(1107,254,'Zimbabwe platinum producers owed $228 million in unpaid export earnings','Zimbabwe\'s\ngovernment owes platinum miners $228 million in unpaid export\nincome under its foreign currency retention system, exerting\npressure on a sector recovering from a price collapse, an\nindustry...','MarketScreener','https://www.marketscreener.com/news/zimbabwe-platinum-producers-owed-228-million-in-unpaid-export-earnings-ce7f5cd2dc8bf127','https://www.marketscreener.com/images/twitter_MS_fdnoir.png','Logistics','Neutral',0,0,'2026-06-19 05:31:38','2026-07-16 10:08:29','2026-07-16 10:09:19');
